# .claudeignore Template for Apprise P&T Team
#
# Purpose: Prevent Claude Code from accessing sensitive files
# Compliance: ISO 27001:2022, Apprise AI Usage Policy, ISMS
# Last Updated: October 2025
#
# INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to your project root as .claudeignore
# 2. Customize the [PROJECT-SPECIFIC] sections for your project
# 3. Verify patterns match your sensitive files: ls -la <pattern>
# 4. Test exclusion: confirm Claude cannot see excluded files
# 5. Keep this file updated as project structure changes
#
# SYNTAX: Same as .gitignore (glob patterns)
# - Use **/ for recursive matching
# - Use * for wildcards
# - Use ! to negate (whitelist)
# - Lines starting with # are comments
#
# ============================================================================
# SECTION 1: SENSITIVE DATA FILES (CLIENT INFORMATION)
# ============================================================================
#
# These patterns prevent Claude from accessing files that may contain:
# - Client PII (names, emails, addresses, phone numbers)
# - Property valuation data
# - Borrower information
# - Sales evidence data
# - Financial information
#
# CRITICAL: These must ALWAYS be excluded

# All CSV files (commonly contain client data)
**/*.csv
*.csv

# Data directories (adjust paths for your project)
**/data/**
**/datasets/**
**/input/**
**/output/**
**/exports/**
**/imports/**

# Client and PII directories
**/client_data/**
**/pii/**
**/personal/**
**/borrower_data/**
**/valuation_data/**
**/sales_evidence/**

# Database files
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
**/*.db
**/database/**

# Excel files (often contain sensitive data)
**/*.xlsx
**/*.xls
*.xlsx
*.xls

# JSON data files (may contain API responses with client data)
**/data/**/*.json
**/responses/**/*.json

# Parquet files (big data formats)
**/*.parquet
*.parquet

# [PROJECT-SPECIFIC] Add your project's data folders here:
# **/my_data_folder/**
# **/valuation_exports/**

